'''Chevak Cup<U+2019>ik''' or just '''Cup<U+2019>ik''' (own name '''Cugtun'''), '''Hooper Bay<U+2013>Chevak Cup<U+2019>ik language'''  is a language or dialect of [[Central Alaskan Yup'ik language|Central Alaskan Yup'ik]] spoken in Central [[Alaska]] in the [[Chevak, Alaska|Chevak]] (own name '''Cev<U+2019>aq''') and [[Hooper Bay, Alaska|Hooper Bay]] by [[Chevak Cup<U+2019>ik people]] (own name '''Cup<U+2019>it''' or '''Cev<U+2019>allrarmuit'''). Actually, Cup<U+2019>ik spoken in Chevak is closer to [[Yugtun|General Central Yup<U+2019>ik]] than it is to [[Nunivak Cup'ig language|Nunivak Cup<U+2019>ig]], therefore they should not be equated. The Cup'ik dialect is threatened. The Yup'ik letter ''c'' is pronounced as an English ''ch''.

The Central Alaskan Yupik who in the village of [[Chevak, Alaska|Chevak]] call themselves ''Cup'ik'' (plural ''Cup'it''). Those who live on [[Nunivak Island]] (''Nuniwar'' in Nunivak Cup'ig, ''Nunivaaq'' in [[Central Alaskan Yup'ik language|Central Yup'ik]]) call themselves ''Cup'ig'' (plural ''Cup'it''). The name '''Cup'ig''' (with g) used for Nunivak Island Yup'ik dialect. But, the name '''Cup'ik''' (with k) used for Hooper Bay-Chevak Yup'ik dialect.

== Education ==
[[File:Chevak.jpg|thumb|right|250px|Chevak, the school (blue), lake, and condemned old school (red)]]
The Cup<U+2019>ik dialect is distinguished from Yup<U+2019>ik by the change of "y" sounds into "ch" sounds, represented by the letter "c", and by some words that are completely different from Yup'ik words.

This unique identity has allowed them to form a single-site [[school district]], the [[Kashunamiut School District]], rather than joining a neighboring Yup<U+2019>ik school district. English and Cup<U+2019>ik bilingual education is done at this school. There is a tri-language system in Chevak; [[English language|English]], Cup<U+2019>ik, and a mixture of the two languages. 

Before 1950 formal education for students in Chevak took place in the ''Qaygiq''<ref>[http://chevakschool.org/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=30&Itemid=48 Qaygiq (Men<U+2019>s House) by Dr. John Pingayak]</ref> (semi-underground men's community house; ''Qasgi'' or ''Qasgiq''<ref>[http://www.yupikscience.org/2qasgi/ Qasgimi : In the Qasgi]</ref> in [[Central Alaskan Yup'ik language|Central Alaskan Yup'ik]]; ''Kiiyar'' in [[Nunivak Cup'ig language|Nunivak Cup<U+2019>ig]]; ''Qargi'' in [[Inupiat language|I<U+00F1>upiaq]]), and in the homes of the people.<ref>[http://www.alaskool.org/native_ed/curriculum/cupik_guidebook/guidebook_cupik.htm Alaskool: Guidebook for Integrating Cup'ik Culture and Curriculum]</ref>

== Classification ==
[[Image:Yukon-Kuskokwim-Delta.png|thumb|right|250px|Central Alaskan Yup'ik-speaking areas]]

*'''[[Central Alaskan Yup'ik language]]'''
**'''Norton Sound dialect''' is spoken [[Norton Sound]] region. Themselves ''Yup<U+2019>ik''
***'''Unaliq subdialect''' by spoken ''Unalirmiut'' (= ''Atnegmiut, Kuuyu<U+014B>miut, E<U+014B>lutale<U+0121>miut'' etc.) tribes.
***'''Kotlik subdialect''' by spoken ''Pastulirmiut'' tribe
**'''General Central Yup<U+2019>ik dialect''' or '''[[Yugtun]]''' is spoken in [[Nelson Island (Alaska)|Nelson Island]], the [[Yukon River|Yukon]], the [[Bristol Bay]] regions, and [[Kuskokwim River|Kuskokwim]]. Themselves ''Yup<U+2019>ik'' (Yukon) or ''Yupiaq'' (Kuskokwim).
**'''[[Egegik Yupik]]''' is spoken [[Egegik, Alaska|Egegik]]. Themselves ''Yup<U+2019>ik''
**'''Hooper Bay-Chevak Cup<U+2019>ik''' is spoken [[Hooper Bay, Alaska|Hooper Bay]] and [[Chevak, Alaska|Chevak]] areas. Themselves ''Cup<U+2019>ik''
**'''[[Nunivak Cup'ig language]]''' or '''dialect''' is spoken [[Nunivak Island]]. Themselves ''Cup<U+2019>ig''

