== Phonology ==
There are 18 letters used in the Cup<U+2019>ik alphabet: '''a c e g i k l m n p q r s t u v w y'''.<ref>http://www.alaskool.org/projects/chevak/chevak/sound1.htm</ref>

These letters are not used in the Cup<U+2019>ik alphabet: '''b d f h j o x z'''.

[[Vowel]]s:
*Short vowels: '''a i u e'''
*Long vowels: '''aa ii uu'''
*Diphthongs:  '''ai ui au iu ua ia'''

[[Consonant]]s:
*Stops: '''p t c k q'''
*Voiced fricatives: '''v l y g r w'''
*Voiceless fricatives: '''vv ll ss gg rr ww'''
*Voiced nasals: '''m''' {{IPA|[m]}} '''n''' {{IPA|[n]}} '''ng''' {{IPA|[<U+014B>]}}
*Voiceless nasals: '''m''' {{IPA|[m<U+0325>]}} '''n''' {{IPA|[n<U+0325>]}} '''ng''' {{IPA|[<U+014B><U+030A>]}}

== Russian loanwords ==
[[Image:Edward S. Curtis Collection People 011.jpg|thumb|right|250px|Hooper Bay youth, 1930]]
The [[Russian language|Russian]] [[loanword]]s used in Chevak Cup<U+2019>ik date from the period of the [[Russian America]] (1733<U+2013>1867).

*'''caarralaq''' (< Rus. ''<U+0441><U+0430><U+0445><U+0430><U+0440>'') 'sugar'
*'''caayuq'''  (< Rus. ''<U+0447><U+0430><U+0439>'') 'tea'
*'''caanik''' (< Rus. ''<U+0447><U+0430><U+0439><U+043D><U+0438><U+043A>'') 'tea kettle'
*'''cap<U+2019>akiq''' ( < Rus. ''<U+0441><U+0430><U+043F><U+043E><U+0433><U+0438>'') 'shoe'
*'''cass<U+2019>aq''' (< Rus. ''<U+0447><U+0430><U+0441><U+044B>'') 'clock'
*'''culunaq''' (?< Rus. ''<U+0441><U+043E><U+043B><U+043E><U+043D><U+0438><U+043D><U+0430>'' 'salted meat') 'salted fish'
*'''kalantaassaq''' (< Rus. ''<U+043A><U+0430><U+0440><U+0430><U+043D><U+0434><U+0430><U+0448>'') 'pencil'
*'''kalmaaniq''' (< Rus. ''<U+043A><U+0430><U+0440><U+043C><U+0430><U+043D>'') 'pocket'
*'''kelipaq''' (< Rus. ''<U+0445><U+043B><U+0435><U+0431>'') 'bread'
*'''luussitaq''' (< Rus. ''<U+043B><U+043E><U+0448><U+0430><U+0434><U+044C>'') 'horse'
*'''mass<U+2019>laq''' (< Rus. ''<U+043C><U+0430><U+0441><U+043B><U+043E>'') 'butter; margarine'
*'''missuulleq''' (< Rus. ''<U+043C><U+0435><U+0448><U+043E><U+043A>'') 'burlap sack'
*'''muluk<U+2019>uuq''' (< Rus. ''<U+043C><U+043E><U+043B><U+043E><U+043A><U+043E>'') 'milk'
*'''mult<U+2019>uuq''' (< Rus. ''<U+043C><U+043E><U+043B><U+043E><U+0442><U+043E><U+043A>'') 'hammer'
*'''pal<U+2019>tuuk''' (< Rus. ''<U+043F><U+0430><U+043B><U+044C><U+0442><U+043E>'') 'coat; jacket'
*'''pelatekaq''' (< Rus. ''<U+043F><U+0430><U+043B><U+0430><U+0442><U+043A><U+0430>'') 'tent'
*'''putuskaq''' (< Rus. ''<U+043F><U+043E><U+0434><U+0443><U+0448><U+043A><U+0430>'') 'pillow'
*'''spickaq''' : (< Rus. ''<U+0441><U+043F><U+0438><U+0447><U+043A><U+0430>'') 'match'
*'''tiititsaaq / tiissitsaaq''' (< Rus. ''<U+0442><U+044B><U+0441><U+044F><U+0447><U+0430>'') 'thousand; one thousand dollars'
*'''yaassiik''' : (< Rus. ''<U+044F><U+0449><U+0438><U+043A>'') 'box; cardboard box'

== The names of days and months ==

*'''erneq''' day
*'''Agayuneq''' ('praying') Sunday
*'''Pekyun''' ('movement')  Monday
*'''Aipirin''' ('next')  Tuesday
*'''Pingayirin''' ('third')  Wednesday
*'''Citamirin''' ('fourth')  Thursday
*'''Tallimirin''' ('fifth')  Friday
*'''Maqineq''' ('steambath')  Saturday

*'''iraluq''' month
*'''Agayuulek''' ('icicles') January
*'''Nakrutlek''' ('accurate shooter') February
*'''Neqlelek''' ('white front geese') March
*'''Tunturalek''' ('reindeer') April
*'''Cupun''' ('breaking river ice') May
*'''Kaugun''' ('clubbing fish') June
*'''Essgun''' ('newly hatched eggs') July
*'''Putukuarun''' ('waddling ducks & geese') August
*'''Amiirairun''' ('shedding') September
*'''Cauyaun''' ('drumming') (in Chevak) / '''Ipukaqun''' (in Hooper Bay) October
*'''Kanruyauciq''' ('frost') November
*'''Angunquyugtuun''' ('big toe') December

